Two problems:

1. You&#39;ve **explicitly** given it a format to parse with (`&quot;d. MMMM YYYY&quot;`), but that format doesn&#39;t remotely match the data you&#39;re providing it (`&quot;2019-06-20&quot;`, etc.).

2. You&#39;re using `d`, not `D`, when formatting. Per [the documentation](https://momentjs.com/docs/#/displaying/), `d` is the day of the *week*, not the day of the month.

If you make the formats correct, it should work:

    let formattedDate = moment(publishDate, &quot;YYYY-MM-DD&quot;).format(
        &quot;D. MMMM YYYY&quot;
    );

Live Example:

&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: true console: false babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-js --&gt;

    $(&quot;.published_date&quot;).each(function() {
        let publishDate = $(this).attr(&quot;data-publish-date&quot;);
        let formattedDate = moment(publishDate, &quot;YYYY-MM-DD&quot;).format(
            &quot;D. MMMM YYYY&quot;
        );
        $(this).text(formattedDate);
    });

&lt;!-- language: lang-html --&gt;

    &lt;span class=&quot;published_date&quot; data-publish-date=&quot;2019-06-20&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;

    &lt;span class=&quot;published_date&quot; data-publish-date=&quot;2019-07-01&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;

    &lt;span class=&quot;published_date&quot; data-publish-date=&quot;2019-08-23&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;

    &lt;script src=&quot;https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/jquery/3.3.1/jquery.min.js&quot;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
    &lt;script src=&quot;https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/moment.js/2.24.0/moment.min.js&quot;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;

&lt;!-- end snippet --&gt;

Since your input is in ISO 8601 recognized format you can use [`moment(String)`][1] and in [`format()`][2] use uppercase `D` is _Day of Month_ instead of lowercase `d` that stands for _Day of Week_

